         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Easter ¶ 1882 ¶ Could you kindly ascertain, dear Mr Jackson, whether in Sir Jam. Smith’s collection, kept by the L.S., any specimen occurs of what Aiton cultivated at Kew as Casuarina stricta. If, as ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.04.09b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To B. Daydon Jackson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Linnean Society of London, Archives, Guard Book 1880-85, f. 112.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Annotated: 'R June/5 July'.</p>
               </note>Easter<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Easter fell on 9 April in 1882.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1882</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Could you kindly ascertain, dear Mr Jackson, whether in Sir Jam. Smith’s collection, kept by the L.S., any specimen occurs of what Aiton cultivated at Kew as <name key="Casuarina%20stricta">Casuarina stricta</name>. If, as he asserts, it came from N. S Wales, it cannot be C. quadrivalvis; on the other hand in 1775 no Ship returned from Port Jackson, but Furneaux came then back from Tasmania.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Furneaux was captain of HMS <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Adventure</seg>, which accompanied James Cook, on HMS <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Resolution</seg>, during the second of his three famous expeditions (1772-5). <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Adventure </seg>but not <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Resolution</seg> visited Tasmania in the course of the expedition.</p>
               </note> C. quadrivalvis is the very reverse of strict<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">stricta?</p>
               </note> in its growth, being more pendulous in its foliage than any other species. The least fragment of Smith’s or Aiton’s plant i.e. the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Kew</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>plant would suffice for me to see, what it was really.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Casuarina%20stricta">Casuarina stricta</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Casuarina%20quadrivalvis">Casuarina quadrivalvis</name>
            </p>
         </div>
